                "href": "/profile/Vincent-Fadoju"
            },
            "answer_text": "Uhm, I\u2019d like to think so.. The truth is, writing mostly comes from your ability to imagine. This includes scenarios, characters and so on. And although being scared helps, it\u2019s not really a factor that would or should stop you from writing in the horror genre. However, most people who write the best horror flicks or even the best horror movies had some level of reality to it. This means that, the writer (the original writer at least) had his horror characters come from a real world experience. It could have been a dream, a metaphor for a real life bad experience or something else entirely. But it\u2019s also important to note that, original ideas about writing horror stories can also come from you and your ability to imagine the scariest of situations. So to answer your question, I\u2019d say it\u2019s very possible. But try to make sure your idea for the writing comes from an original place as that helps in developing your characters in the long run..\ud83d\ude07 ",
